Turkey expands its diplomatic horizons
Long before Turkey tried to join the European Union, European powers were keen to penetrate the country's interior.
On the eastern side of the Bosphorus, perhaps just 20 paces inland into Asia, lies one of the most interesting relics of disastrous imperial ambition.
Hydarpasha railway station was designed by two German architects, Otto Ritter and Helmut Conu, in neo-Renaissance style.
