"A week ago", explained Toshihide Mizuno, the MUFG's chief executive, in Tokyo, "we thought the stake would have been made up of ordinary shares only.
But in view of the current economic and market situation, we wanted to minimise risks and cover ourselves. "
On the basis of the weighted average price, MUFG will pay its Morgan Stanley securities 7% below their book value.
And the transaction will result in a dilution of about 20% of earnings per share.
